                            "category": "Options",
                            "categoryID": 65,
                            "keyword": "No COT- We get Env Lien",
                            "sectionID": 30,
                            "text": "<p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">A chain-of-title search consists of all real property records of deeds and easements on the subject property as maintained by the Clark County Clerk. The review is performed to identify previous land owners who may have conducted environmentally hazardous operations which could adversely impact the subject property. A 50-year chain-of-title was not provided to Benchmark by Verizon Wireless for review.</font></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">&nbsp;</font></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">An Environmental Lien Search and the most recent Deed were provided by EDR. No environmentally significant easements, liens, or activity and use limitations were found filed on the subject property. The property was transferred by Quitclaim Deed from Providence Plaza, LLC to Providence Centre, LLC on December 23, 2014.</font></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">&nbsp;</font></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">Title information is included in Appendix E, Title Documents.</font></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px\"><font color=\"#ff0000\">&nbsp;</font></p><p><span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\">The review did not indicate any operations which may pose an environmental concern to the subject property. No environmental liens or activity and use limitations were identified.</span></p>",
