                                    "keyword": "Long Term Ag Use ",
                                    "sectionID": 194,
                                    "text": "<span>The historical use of the subject property as farm land indicates potential use of agricultural chemicals such as pesticides, herbicides and fertilizers at the subject property; however, proper use of agricultural chemicals would be considered a de minimis condition and not a release under CERCLA; therefore, not a recognized environmental condition to the subject property.</span>",
